Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.91,0:00:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,On tonight’s “Lincoln,” we present in full {\i1}the incident{\i0} that stirred all of Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.33,0:00:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten days ago, Japanese internet users were in a tumult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.34,0:00:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The incident that was even covered by Yahoo! News...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.14,0:00:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We present the whole truth tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.73,0:00:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The members are made to wait in a renewed classroom set of “The Lecturer".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.91,0:00:35.91,[Hotohara],Ho,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.82,0:00:44.10,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,{\pos(225,334)}He opened the door so hard
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.92,0:00:44.10,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,he surprised himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.15,0:00:45.42,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,It’s like how an animal reacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.55,0:00:46.86,[Amano],Amano,0,0,0,,He can’t gauge himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.86,0:00:48.66,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,He went “boom!” and he’s the one most freaked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.66,0:00:52.06,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,He was the closest to the door.  Because the “boom!” was closest to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.06,0:00:53.80,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.13,0:00:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hamada is the teacher? Mr. Hamada?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.98,0:00:58.67,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.67,0:01:01.87,[Otake],,0,0,0,,He used to sit with us together, right!?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.60,0:01:04.44,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Ok, I mean, good morning, but, you’re always sitting here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.44,0:01:08.91,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,From this time, this is {\alpha&HFF&\t(758,200,\alpha&H00&)}“The {\alpha&HFF&\t(1559,200,\alpha&H00&)}New Lecturer,” so…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.64,0:01:11.65,[Mimura],Mim,0,0,0,,But if Mr. Hamada is the teacher, then that’s going to be for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.64,0:01:16.56,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,No… I’m going to be your homeroom teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.56,0:01:19.69,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,And for every episode a special lecturer will be coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.69,0:01:22.26,[Otake],Otake,0,0,0,,So there won’t be that strong… “pressure” coming from the homeroom teacher then?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.26,0:01:24.46,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,That will depend on the time and place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.90,0:01:27.17,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,That can’t be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.17,0:01:28.52,Default,All,0,0,0,,What…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.52,0:01:30.50,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,The classroom has been renovated and improved.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.70,0:01:34.27,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Everyone’s uniforms, as well, from those dirty tracksuits you had before.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.27,0:01:36.00,[Mimura],Mim,0,0,0,,Like private school.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.74,0:01:36.77,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,It’s like those nice ones that rich kids wear, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.77,0:01:38.88,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,It looks smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.88,0:01:41.41,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,And now for our special lecturer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.10,0:01:43.22,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Please come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.16,0:01:47.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Who is the new lecturer?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.88,0:01:49.52,[Rola],Rola,0,0,0,,Bam!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.00,0:01:50.77,[Rola],Rola,0,0,0,,Ok!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.16,0:01:54.86,[Miyasako],Miy,0,0,0,,The other door, the other door.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.40,0:01:59.40,[Hamada],Hamada,0,0,0,,Our teacher is Miss Rola!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.11,0:02:10.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Tonight’s lecturer, looking surprisingly good in a teacher’s outfit is the 23-year-old Rola.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:16.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What sort of lecture will they receive from a teacher who is twenty years younger than them?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.88,0:02:19.40,[Rola],,0,0,0,,I am angry today!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.45,0:02:24.66,Default,All,0,0,0,,You’re not angry at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.66,0:02:27.01,[Rola],,0,0,0,,I am! Huff, puff…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.01,0:02:29.13,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,The teacher is angry. Listen properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.13,0:02:30.33,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,You’re angry at us?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.33,0:02:31.41,[Rola],,0,0,0,,That’s right!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.83,0:02:34.47,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,We haven’t done anything to be angered at.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.47,0:02:37.49,[Rola],,0,0,0,,You have!  First, here I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.74,0:02:39.17,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,“First, here I go….”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.74,0:02:42.01,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,The teacher is speaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.23,0:02:48.91,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Ok. {\alpha&HFF&\t(1400,200,\alpha&H00&)}This is my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.73,0:02:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We know…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.35,0:02:53.02,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,You’re pretty famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.02,0:02:57.89,[Matsumoto],Matsumoto,0,0,0,,I say “Rola” more than “Saijo Hideki”{a famous singer}. Really.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.29,0:03:02.73,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Starting from Miyasako, please introduce yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.53,0:03:03.93,Default,All,0,0,0,,Whoa, that’s scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.47,0:03:05.03,[Miyasako],Miy,0,0,0,,A self-introduction?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.22,0:03:05.03,[Rola],Rola,0,0,0,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.03,0:03:06.74,[Rola],Rola,0,0,0,,Like where do you live…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.77,0:03:09.40,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,Personal information like that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.40,0:03:10.67,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,The teacher told you to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.67,0:03:13.91,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,Personal information like that in a self-introduction!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.91,0:03:16.48,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,Your address! Say your address!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.48,0:03:19.18,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Mr. Mimura! {\alpha&HFF&\t(1050,200,\alpha&H00&)}A self-introduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.28,0:03:22.18,[Rola],,0,0,0,,What food do you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.18,0:03:24.05,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,Um, sukiyaki
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:25.62,[Rola],,0,0,0,,I love sukiyaki, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.38,0:03:27.52,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.79,0:03:30.32,[Rola],,0,0,0,,{\clip(0,262,11,400)\t(0,1750,\clip(0,262,712,400))}Do you dip it in egg when you eat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.93,0:03:36.16,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,An explanation of sukiyaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.77,0:03:37.64,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.60,0:03:40.37,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Matsumoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.37,0:03:43.04,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Tell us like where you grew up…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.04,0:03:45.27,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Like where you grew up or I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.27,0:03:50.68,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Ok, where did you go for Golden Week?
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.77,0:03:50.68,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,{\pos(491,321)}That’s totally different!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.77,0:03:50.68,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Thas has nothing to do with that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.68,0:03:51.78,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Where I grew up?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.91,0:03:56.82,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,What he did for Golden Week, is what you’d like to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.45,0:03:56.82,[Rola],,0,0,0,,{\pos(212,329)}Yeah, I'm curious!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.57,0:03:56.82,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,For Golden Week?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.82,0:04:01.12,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,I was at home at times, {\alpha&HFF&\t(1500,200,\alpha&H00&)}I went to the park as well at times…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.12,0:04:02.99,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Huh? Which park?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.10,0:04:07.90,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,I don’t know the exact name of the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.90,0:04:10.46,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,It wasn’t a famous park or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.46,0:04:13.53,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Oh, really. Did you like jump-rope or— were you playing a lot there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.53,0:04:15.83,[Otake],Otake,0,0,0,,It’s not like he went there alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.83,0:04:18.14,[Rola],,0,0,0,,What did you play there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.86,0:04:20.37,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Well, I mean, I brought my daughter there...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.37,0:04:22.54,[Rola],,0,0,0,,What, you have a daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.54,0:04:26.85,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,{\clip(25,25,11,400)\t(0,1750,\clip(25,25,712,400))}Do you know absolutely nothing about me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.91,0:04:26.13,[Rola],,0,0,0,,{\pos(360,363)}Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.44,0:04:28.61,[Rola],,0,0,0,,{\pos(360,363)}That’s cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.89,0:04:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would he go to the park alone to play jump-rope at his age?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.78,0:04:33.05,[Rola],,0,0,0,,That’s really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.11,0:04:43.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Rola, on her A-game, thoroughly teases the members at her own pace.  She then reveals the topic of tonight’s lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.06,0:04:48.23,[Rola],,0,0,0,,What I am angrily huffing and puffing about is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.78,0:04:47.40,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Yes, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.70,0:04:50.41,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,She’s going to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.41,0:04:51.30,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.89,0:04:53.38,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,Just erase it if you want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.14,0:04:58.64,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,{\pos(521,327)}She has long legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.52,0:04:58.64,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Do you know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.47,0:05:00.31,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Twitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.31,0:05:02.01,Default,All,0,0,0,,Yeah, Twitter. Heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.65,0:05:04.01,[Rola],,0,0,0,,In English, it’s “Twitter.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.01,0:05:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.38,0:05:08.07,[Otake],,0,0,0,,What’s that about?  I didn’t know you had that kind of thing going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.69,0:05:08.59,[Rola],,0,0,0,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.59,0:05:11.46,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Are you all on Twitter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.84,0:05:14.56,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,People who are on Twitter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.09,0:05:14.10,[Otake],,0,0,0,,Just Miyasako?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.10,0:05:15.00,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,Just me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.24,0:05:17.88,[Hotohara],,0,0,0,,{\pos(447,336)}I have been on Twitter before!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.88,0:05:19.77,[Hotohara],,0,0,0,,{\pos(500,336)}I’m not on it anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.80,0:05:20.27,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,So that’s just Miyasako, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.27,0:05:21.40,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,The others aren’t doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.95,0:05:24.44,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,I really have no clue how it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:26.84,[Rola],,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.02,0:05:30.61,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Teacher, what are you "huffing and puffing" angrily about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.99,0:05:33.65,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Because {\alpha&HFF&\t(775,200,\alpha&H00&)}everyone isn't on {\fnClannad Round\fs34\1c&HFFAC00&\4c&H9925DD&}Twitter{\fnFranklin Gothic Medium} !
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.67,0:05:39.25,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Who wouldn’t be on Twitter in this day and age?  That's what she’s angry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.50,0:05:41.49,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,You’re all behind the times.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.49,0:05:46.93,[Rola],,0,0,0,,So today I’m here to force everyone to get on {\fnClannad Round\fs34\1c&HFFAC00&\4c&H9925DD&}Twitter{\fnFranklin Gothic Medium} !
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.35,0:05:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Social media evolves at a dizzying pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lincoln members have not been paying attention and have been left behind by technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.90,0:05:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This cannot continue!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.81,0:06:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So this episode, Rola’s lecture is: “Let’s all start Twitter.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.40,0:06:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Rola is actually one of the most popular Twitter users in Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.14,0:06:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,having the fourth-most Twitter followers in Japan after people like Ariyoshi and Son Masayoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.29,0:06:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Rola, with her credentials of 1,440,000 followers, brings a revolution to Lincoln!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.64,0:06:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.90,0:06:26.97,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Everyone, don’t be like Mr. Matsumoto, ok?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.46,0:06:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto embarrasses himself with his first tweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.14,0:06:32.56,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,I want to tweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.09,0:06:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re tweeting too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.80,0:06:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,These middle-aged comedians have avoided the internet until now –
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.04,0:06:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we document their foray into Twitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.31,0:06:46.08,[Hotohara],,0,0,0,,It’s unbelievable that Mr. Matsumoto would be on Twitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.66,0:06:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The Twitter incident that believe-it-or-not was taken up by Yahoo! News – here we present in full.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.90,0:07:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A breath of fresh air to Lincoln: Rola’s "The New Lecturer."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.10,0:07:05.00,[Rola],,0,0,0,,So why are you on Twitter, Mr. Miyasako?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.00,0:07:08.23,[Miyasako],Miyasako,0,0,0,,There was a TV program that…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.23,0:07:12.12,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,that asked, would you try this for a segment?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.14,0:07:12.12,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Oh, that’s how—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.12,0:07:15.68,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,That’s how I started and—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.68,0:07:17.52,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,and Hoto quit after a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.52,0:07:19.42,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Why did you quit?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.42,0:07:22.36,[Hotohara],,0,0,0,,I hadn’t gone golfing in a while so I tweeted, “I want to go golfing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.36,0:07:27.16,[Hotohara],,0,0,0,,Then I got a reply from someone I didn’t know who said, “That’d be wasted on a guy like you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.46,0:07:30.20,[Hotohara],Fling,0,0,0,,{\move(177,293,537,337,1400,1400)\t(1450,100,\fr-10)}So I got pissed, threw it away, \N{\alpha&HFF&}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.20,0:07:32.33,[Hotohara],Fling,0,0,0,,{\fr-10\move(537,337,-250,95,1150,500)}So I got pissed, threw it away,\Nand I quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.33,0:07:36.15,Caption Wizard,,0,0,0,,{\pos(485,316)}No wonder he quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.33,0:07:33.36,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Yeah, that’s uncalled for.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.57,0:07:34.56,[Hotohara],,0,0,0,,That’s how I quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.30,0:07:36.15,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,That makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.15,0:07:38.70,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,No way you deserved to have that, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.84,0:07:38.70,[Hotohara],,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.17,0:07:39.40,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,That’s the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.40,0:07:41.44,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,{\pos(350,387)}That sort of thing could happen, which is \N\Nwhy I don’t really want to do it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.86,0:07:45.34,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Oh, really.  {\alpha&HFF&\t(2370,200,\alpha&H00&)}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.97,0:07:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than Miyasako, it seems that people have a negative view of the Twitter experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.98,0:07:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So Rola starts by teaching the positives of the Twitter experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.09,0:08:02.56,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,So these are the positives of the Twitter experience according to the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.88,0:08:02.56,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.56,0:08:03.66,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.64,0:08:05.73,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Circle number one:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.43,0:08:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t need that part.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.61,0:08:10.14,[Rola],,0,0,0,,You can make friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.22,0:08:13.12,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Circle number two:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.12,0:08:14.58,[Rola],,0,0,0,,You get information.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.86,0:08:19.31,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Like current events, {\alpha&HFF&\t(800,200,\alpha&H00&)}political things— {\alpha&HFF&\t(2030,200,\alpha&H00&)}you would want to get the news about that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.31,0:08:21.58,[Rola],,0,0,0,,You can really get updated on things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.83,0:08:23.25,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,It’ll tell us about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:23.25,[Rola],,0,0,0,,{\pos(348,327)}Yup, it will.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.25,0:08:25.58,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Circle number three: You can become popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.82,0:08:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.85,0:08:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Become popular?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.02,0:08:29.69,[Otake],,0,0,0,,Among whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.59,0:08:29.69,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Among whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.90,0:08:33.26,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Among the people who are, like, walking around on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.26,0:08:36.43,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,I think there are more people who aren’t walking around on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.43,0:08:38.70,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Miyasako, the only one of us on Twitter, would you say these are right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.44,0:08:39.46,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,Yes, things that you really wouldn’t know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.46,0:08:43.93,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,For example, I might say “I went to a really good ramen place.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.93,0:08:49.27,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,Then replies like “This other place is good”, “This place is better,” information like that comes right to you all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.64,0:08:54.15,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,{\pos(308,287)}In general, most of it is messages of support!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.88,0:08:54.15,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Most of it is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.15,0:08:55.30,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Yeah, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.18,0:08:58.05,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,How often do you tweet, Miss Rola?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.76,0:09:02.15,[Rola],,0,0,0,,{\clip(30,309,43,400)\t(500,2500,\clip(30,309,675,400)}Hmm, I haven't tweeted at all these couple of days.  \N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.95,0:09:05.82,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,And then you’re telling everyone to “Go, go do Twitter!”?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.93,0:09:06.32,Default,Mim,0,0,0,,That doesn’t make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.88,0:09:09.93,[Hotohara],,0,0,0,,Don’t you tweet a lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.29,0:09:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t seem like simply tweeting a lot will always increase your number of followers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.09,0:09:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What are show businesses personalities on Twitter with a lot of followers tweeting about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.55,0:09:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at the tweets of popular Twitter users.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.58,0:09:32.02,[Hamada] - Align Left,,0,0,0,,{\pos(57,347)}Now, everyone, {\alpha&HFF&\t(1400,200,\alpha&H00&)}are you curious about what \N\N{\alpha&HFF&\t(3280,200,\alpha&H00&)}{\1c&H9925DD&}Miss Rola {\1c&HED3635&}tweets about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.56,0:09:32.02,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,This is Miss Rola, the fourth most popular Twitter user.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.02,0:09:34.45,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,It can be short, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.88,0:09:33.76,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.45,0:09:37.13,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Mr. Miyasako, what does this part here mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.13,0:09:41.99,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,That’s where a follower, a regular person, is asking a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.99,0:09:43.69,[Rola],,0,0,0,,This is what someone wrote to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.26,0:09:50.07,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Don’t say it first!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.79,0:09:50.07,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.07,0:09:52.98,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Someone said “If you use English first, you lose,” and you replied with “Ok” {[in English]}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.98,0:09:55.01,[Amano],,0,0,0,,So you lost there as a joke, ahh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.01,0:09:58.00,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,“I’m starting to go bald.  What do I do?  Rola, tell me!”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.04,0:10:01.65,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Ahh! Just stick something on there~.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:04.85,[Otake],,0,0,0,,{\pos(584,288)}How crude!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.74,0:10:07.95,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Well, there is some truth there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.30,0:10:07.95,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.61,0:10:12.78,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Lastly, “What is that on Mr. Gushiken’s head?"*
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.61,0:10:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fs18}*Gushiken Yoko is a former Japanese boxer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.74,0:10:13.74,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Broccoli!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.08,0:10:16.86,[Udo],Am,0,0,0,,{\pos(507,312)}This is like {\fs34\1c&00&\4c&H083D85&\b900\fnLucida Handwriting}ogiri{\fnFranklin Gothic Medium\1c&H083D85&\4c&00&}  !
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.98,0:10:19.40,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,This, {\alpha&HFF&\t(830,200,\alpha&H00&)}this is the fourth most popular Twitter user.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.40,0:10:20.83,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Fourth place in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.83,0:10:24.13,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,It’s like ogiri, so, it’s tiring, you know? {MATCH THE SUBTITLE/Fix this later}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.80,0:10:27.83,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,To see what popular users are tweeting…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.83,0:10:29.01,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,For example, this person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.14,0:10:33.41,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,{\pos(459,370)}Oh, RG is popular!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.73,0:10:32.63,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Believe it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.41,0:10:35.68,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,He’s popular for his “Did you ever notice”-type of jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.21,0:10:41.64,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,“A ‘Did you ever notice’ joke for this once-in-a-decade cold wave we're having, please!”, someone tweeted him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.64,0:10:42.77,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,RG replied,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.67,0:10:48.46,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,“The news on TV tends to show shots of people slipping on frozen sidewalks.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.73,0:10:52.57,[Amano],,0,0,0,,So you can just give a straight answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.31,0:10:56.27,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,For us in the business, it wasn’t that funny.  But for regular people, maybe…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.83,0:11:01.67,[Amano],,0,0,0,,It was a very RG-type of joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.99,0:11:05.01,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,“A conveyor belt sushi ‘Did you ever notice’ joke, please.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:08.25,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,“Tends to expand the possibilities of mayonnaise.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.76,0:11:11.35,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,They’re getting better!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.38,0:11:16.05,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,One more person.  Please take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.46,0:11:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Wakky.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.91,0:11:20.22,[Rola],,0,0,0,,{\pos(391,370)}Oh, Wakky is on, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.60,0:11:22.89,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Wakky is popular for his face bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.89,0:11:25.70,[Otake],,0,0,0,,You can post photos, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.00,0:11:25.70,[Miyasako],,0,0,0,,{\pos(207,332)}Yes, you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.45,0:11:27.50,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.50,0:11:30.61,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,“I’m feeling down this morning.  Cheer me up!”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.70,0:11:33.40,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,Wakky replies with the title “Face!”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.73,0:11:41.50,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,He looks like he's giving it his all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.58,0:11:44.72,[Amano],,0,0,0,,He put some time into that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.24,0:11:45.53,[Rola],,0,0,0,,Eww.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.53,0:11:48.15,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,He's giving it his all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.15,0:11:51.72,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Even if I could do that face,  {\fs36\alpha&HFF&\t(1225,200,\alpha&H00&)}I probably wouldn’t do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.99,0:12:01.17,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,“Nothing much happened today, so can I get a 'nothing' face?”  He replied with “Face!”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.84,0:12:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s definitely a "nothing" face.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.64,0:12:10.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Other than those, there were requests like, {Double check timings}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.54,0:12:19.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,“Please give me a face that will energize me” and “Congratulate me on my birthday” to which Wakky gave his faces with full effort. {Double check timings}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.48,0:12:22.82,[Hamada] - Align Left,,0,0,0,,{\pos(70,386)}He put this much in \N\N{\alpha&HFF&\t(860,200,\alpha&H00&)}and he has {\1c&H1914D0&\4c&HED3635&\alpha&HFF&\t(1500,200,\alpha&H00&)}18,000 {\1c&HED3635&\4c&00&}followers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.67,0:12:27.29,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,{\pos(415,289)}Even after giving it his all like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.82,0:12:27.54,[Hotohara],,0,0,0,,I haven’t done anything in years.
