Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.97,0:39:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, of course you’re allowed to continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.82,0:39:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s take a look at some of the exchanges the members had that became popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.48,0:39:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This tweet by Matsumoto was how it began.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.47,0:39:19.74,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,I didn’t have anything to tweet about,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.74,0:39:22.68,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,so being almost Hamada’s birthday, I tweeted,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.68,0:39:24.91,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,“Like I got anything to do with that!”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.51,0:39:31.25,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,, This is where the hell started.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.25,0:39:33.55,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Everyone would— the members would tweet all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.55,0:39:35.72,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,These would normally go to Hamada.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.72,0:39:39.96,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,But Hamada’s not on Twitter so they all came to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.29,0:39:41.38,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,“Congratulations, Mr. Hamada!”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.81,0:39:42.89,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,Since Mr. Matsumoto is the closest to Mr. Hamada.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.89,0:39:43.98,[Hamada],,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.33,0:39:45.18,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Mimura sent one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.18,0:39:51.40,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,“Thanks, Mimura.  Such a happy occasion.  Like I got anything to do with that!” I tsukkomi-ed again.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.78,0:39:51.40,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,A play-along tsukkomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.40,0:39:57.20,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,The play-along tsukkomi, it keeps coming.  Udo ,all over here.  “Happy Birthday, Mr. Hamada!”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.69,0:40:01.01,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,After a while, I got tired,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.50,0:40:04.80,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,and I was saying “Like I got anything to do with that!”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.98,0:40:09.12,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,But it still wouldn’t stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.12,0:40:12.02,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,It still wouldn’t stop, so I just gave up and said, “I’m gonna go buy a present.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.02,0:40:13.10,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,You were broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.30,0:40:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He just went along with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.43,0:40:16.56,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,But it still kept going.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.86,0:40:22.00,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,It still kept going.  Here, from Amano.  From Hoto, too, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.40,0:40:22.90,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.00,0:40:24.00,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,“Completely late.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.10,0:40:30.68,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,“Congratulations.” There was no use, so I thought if it comes to this, “It’s a party! Don’t tell Hamada.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.63,0:40:33.00,[Mimura],,0,0,0,,“Going to bed.”  The End.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.15,0:40:35.30,[Amano],,0,0,0,,That was a sign meaning “The End.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.80,0:40:39.28,[Matsumoto],,0,0,0,,This whole time was really tiring.
